To explore the use of cavity free EPs for light harvesting and energy transport we study their spatiotemporal dynamics using femtosecond transient absorption microscopy (fs-TAM) as shown in Fig. 3a. Here, a broadband sub-10 fs pump pulse (520 – 650 nm) is focussed to the diffraction limit (FWHM ~270 nm) by a high numerical aperture (~1.1) objective onto the sample, with a wide field, counter-propagating probe pulse (8 fs, 680 – 790 nm, FWHM ~15 μm) focussed with a concave mirror, used to monitor the normalised change in image transmission with pump on (Ton) and off (Toff) as function of time delay between the pulses (△TT=Ton−ToffToff\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
